  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Preheat the oven and cook the potatoes </strong></p>\n<p>Set to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7 and boil a kettle. </p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces, add them to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and cook them for 10-12 minutes or until they're fork-tender.</p>\n<p>Once cooked, drain and set them aside. Reserve the pot for later.</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Render the duck skin </strong></p>\n<p>Whilst the potatoes are boiling, use a sharp knife to score the <strong>duck skin</strong> on a diagonal, being careful not to cut through to the meat. Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>.</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>scored duck</strong>, skin-side down, to a cold dry pan over a low-medium heat. Cook for 10-15 minutes, skin-side down only, or until the <strong>skin</strong> is golden and crispy and the fat under the skin rendered. </p>\n<p>Tip: By cooking this over a low-medium heat, you'll render all of the fat.</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Roast the duck fat potatoes </strong></p>\n<p>Once golden, transfer the <strong>duck</strong>, skin-side up, to a baking tray and set aside until later. Reserve the <strong>duck fat</strong> for your potatoes.</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>drained potatoes</strong> to a separate baking tray, crush gently with a fork and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>.<strong> </strong>Pour over the reserved<strong> duck fat </strong>and give everything a good mix up.</p>\n<p>Put the <strong>potatoes</strong> in the oven for 30-35 minutes or until golden and crisp.</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Prepare to make your orange sauce</strong></p>\n<p>Whilst the potatoes are in the oven, zest 1<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2]</span> <strong>orange<span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span></strong>. Try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter!</p>\n<p>Peel and finely dice the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>.</p>\n<p>Dissolve 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>Knorr</strong> <strong>chicken stock cube</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>.</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-4-new-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-4-new-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-4-new-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-4-new-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-4-new-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Start cooking the sauce and roast the duck</strong></p>\n<p>Heat a pot with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat. Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and cook for 3-4 minutes or until softened.</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, put the<strong> duck breasts</strong> in the oven for 10-12 minutes for <strong>medium</strong>. Cook for a further 3-5 minutes if you prefer your duck <strong>well done</strong>. Once cooked, set the <strong>duck</strong> aside to rest for at least 10 minutes. </p>\n<p>Tip: Resting your duck will keep it moist and tender!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1556.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Finish your orange sauce</strong></p>\n<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>honey</strong>, <strong>chicken stock</strong> and the <strong>juice</strong> of the <strong>oranges</strong> to the pot and bring to a boil over a high heat. Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-high and cook for 10-15 minutes or until the sauce is thick and sticky.</p>\n<p>Once sticky, stir in the <strong>orange zest</strong> – this is your <strong>orange sauce</strong>.</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
